        "image_position": "right",
        "eyebrow": "Ultrafiltration",
        "heading": "Membrane Filtration, Without The Waste.",
        "body_text": "Ultrafiltration pushes water through a hollow-fiber membrane with pores measured in nanometers — small enough to block sediment, bacteria, and cysts, while letting water flow through at full pressure. Unlike reverse osmosis, it produces zero wastewater and needs no electricity or drain line, so it fits anywhere a countertop can. HAUSTAS Pure and Pure One both run on this technology, paired with carbon and KDF stages for taste and heavy-metal reduction.",
